# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/language-service 10.x 11.x

### Is this a regression?
Not sure if this affects previous versions. I've seen it in 10 and 11.

### Description
Language service loses typing when type is inferred from an overloaded function. I added a screenshot from WebStorm.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
```typescript
interface State {
  object: { prop: string; };
}

interface Service<T> {
  select<A = T>(op: OperatorFunction<T, A>): Observable<A>;
  select<K1 extends keyof T>(k1: K1): Observable<T[K1]>;

  select<A = T, B = A>(op1: OperatorFunction<T, A>, op2: OperatorFunction<A, B>): Observable<B>;
  select<K1 extends keyof T, K2 extends keyof T[K1]>(k1: K1, k2: K2): Observable<T[K1][K2]>;

  selectNotOverloaded<K1 extends keyof T, K2 extends keyof T[K1]>(k1: K1, k2: K2): Observable<T[K1][K2]>;
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html'
})
export class AppComponent {
  service: Service<{ state: State }> = {} as any;

  object$ = this.service.select('state', 'object');
  object2$ = this.service.selectNotOverloaded('state', 'object');
  objectWithMap$ = this.service.select('state').pipe(map(s => s.object));
}
```
