### Is this a regression?
Not sure if this affects previous versions. I've seen it in 10 and 11.

### Description
Language service loses the type when used with generics and null in optional chaining. I added a screenshot from WebStorm.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
```typescript
interface ObjectType {
  prop: string;
}
interface StateGenericWithNull<T> {
  object?: T | null;
}
interface StateGeneric<T> {
  object?: T;
}
interface StateWithNull {
  object?: ObjectType | null;
}
interface State {
  object?: ObjectType;
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html'
})
export class AppComponent {
  stateGenericWithNull: StateGenericWithNull<ObjectType> = {};
  stateGeneric: StateGeneric<ObjectType> = {};
  stateWithNull: StateWithNull = {};
  state: State = {};
}
